text: Mohamad Naser Al Sayed (born November 2, 1981) is a Qatari chess Grandmaster (since 2009). He is ranked 2nd best player in Qatar. As of December, 2015, his FIDE Elo rating is 2520. ==Performance in competitions== Al-Sayed claimed the 3rd Arab elite chess championship title in Dubai, in June 2015. He has played for Qatar at eleven chess Olympiads since 1994. == References == Category:1981 births Category:Chess grandmasters Category:Living people Category:Qatari chess players Category:Chess players at the 2006 Asian Games Category:Chess players at the 2010 Asian Games Category:Asian Games competitors for Qatar
